---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pallet Wrapping — Formic"
  description="Automated stretch-wrapping cells. Tight, consistent wraps that survive the truck — under Formic Full Service."
  ogTitle="Pallet Wrapping — Formic"
  ogDescription="Tight wraps, dock-ready. Automated stretch-wrap cells under Formic Full Service."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/pallet-wrapping" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Pallet Wrapping
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Pallet Wrapping</div>
    <h1>Tight wraps,<br><em>dock-ready.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Automated stretch-wrap cells that consistently wrap, label, and stage finished pallets — running directly from the palletizer to the dock without operator intervention.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/PalletWrapping-Robopac.webp">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Stretch-wrap cell · production cycle</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>The wrap is <em>where loads fail</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most pallet damage in transit traces back to inconsistent wrap. Manual wrapping is one of the most variable steps on the floor — film tension, layer count, and corner coverage shift between operators and shifts. Automation locks all three in.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Consistent film tension on every wrap</li>
        <li>Programmable layer count and corner coverage by SKU</li>
        <li>Significant reduction in transit-damage chargebacks</li>
        <li>Lower film consumption per pallet vs. manual baseline</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Scope my line →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/PalletWrapping-Robopac.webp" alt="Automated stretch-wrap cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Programmable wrap profile</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/PalletWrapping-Robopac.webp">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Inline · palletizer to dock</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Inline Integration</div>
      <h2>Palletizer to <em>dock</em>, untouched.</h2>
      <p>The wrap cell sits directly downstream of the palletizer on a powered conveyor. Wrap profile auto-selects based on pallet ID; a label printer applies the BOL. The pallet shows up at the dock door already shipping-ready.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Direct conveyor handoff from palletizer or AMR drop-zone</li>
        <li>Auto-select wrap profile from pallet ID or SKU</li>
        <li>Inline print-and-apply labeling option</li>
        <li>Throughput up to 60 pallets/hour, profile-dependent</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Specs</div>
      <h2>Configurable to <em>any pallet</em>.</h2>
      <p>Rotary turntable, rotary arm, or robotic mobile wrapper — we spec to your floor space, throughput, and pallet mix.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Pallet sizes: 36×36" to 48×48", custom export sizes available</li>
        <li>Stack height: up to 96"</li>
        <li>Film: 60 – 250% pre-stretch, 1 – 6 layers programmable</li>
        <li>Configurations: rotary turntable, rotary arm, mobile wrapper</li>
        <li>Safety: light curtains, area scanners, full ANSI/RIA R15.06 compliance</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Get a quote →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Wrapped pallet staged at dock" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Dock-ready · labeled</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Talos-0143.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Wrap · label · stage</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Stop losing pallets<br><em>on the truck.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
